                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 365.117/175.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Page</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 29, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>398. Department’s 332, September 28. War Office now asks for family history
                    Ajello, which Embassy obtaining from him at Naples. In presenting information
                    desired, will make another urgent appeal for his release.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy.</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
